Exercise 1

Rockefeller University, Bioinformatics Resource Centre

https://rockefelleruniversity.github.io/scRNA-seq

 

These exercises are about manipulate single-cell data with Seurat. Please download the counting matrix from BOX and loading them into a Seurat object. Or you may also used the rds file data/scSeq_CKO_1kCell_ori.rds.

Exercise 1 - Data manipulation with Seurat

loading data

  1. Please create a Seurat object by reading counting data from BOX or by loading the rds file. Then calculate mitochondrial contents of each ell

Basi QC plot

  1. Please access the read counts (nCount_RNA), gene counts (nFeature_RNA), and mitochondrial content (percent.mt) for each cell and draw violin plot

  2. Please made a dot plot for nCount_RNA vs nFeature_RNA and try to point out potential doublets

  3. Please made a dot plot for nount_RNA vs percent.mt and try to point out potential cell debris

  4. Please remove cells with percent.mt >= 10 for following analysis
